The voyage from the space station started 3 -1/2 hours earlier, when it undocked and began a slow, gentle drift away.

It made a perfect landing in the still and summery weather at 2:14pm local time, right on schedule.

Commenting on the landing, NASA TV reporter Rob Navias described it as 'a bullseye.'

Kononenko was the first to be extracted from the descent module.

